radiographic_examinations.findings: Single frontal chest radiograph demonstrates right-sided pneumoperitoneum evident under the right hemidiaphragm with adjacent compressive atelectasis. A retrocardiac opacification is likely a combination of atelectasis and eventration of the hemidiaphragm. Cardiomediastinal and hilar contours are unremarkable. No pleural effusions evident though the left costophrenic angle is obscured from view.
